<br>
Route #1- from Sol A:  Go to the room just before you turn to go to Lysandra (sp?, she drops the sparkle purse) where the Solusek Priest spawns, there is a ramp leading down that it kinda splits, left going to the zone line to Sol B, the right path going up a small ramp.  Go up the small ramp to the pool of Lava.  Jump in (yes, it burns!) and swim (under-lava) thru the tunnel to the zone (welcome to Sol C, ouch, hot, ooh, ouch!), and as Doris says, &quot;just keep swimming swimming swimming&quot; till you hit the rocky beach.  If you go through the zone line to Sol B, you will be at the bridge with the hole in it (see route #2 below).<br>
<br>
Route #2- from Sol B:  You can either zone in from Sol A to Sol B at the zone behind line behind the Solusek Priest area, or if you want to do it from the Sol B/Lavastorm zone line , here is how.  Upon entering the zone, run forward thru the first room, then follow the left wall until you come to the stone trap.  Run under the trap and hang a right into Bat-1.  Turn left in Bat-1 and follow the left wall through Bat-2 until you come to the Nox spider room (at least I ahve seen it spawn there).  Just keep following the left wall until you come to a bridge over the lava river just before you hit the zone line to Sol A.  You know you are at the right place because the bridge has a hole in the middle of it.<br>
  Turn to face the lava waterfall on your left (upstream!).  Get on your levitation spell and run across and stand on top of the lava, then drop lev.  Splash!  Burn! Burn!  Swim upstream **UNDER THE LAVA** (very important - if you cross the zone line above the lava you will end up in SOl A) through the zone line (welcome to Sol C) and keep swimming until you hit the beach.  Do I need to remind you that it burns?<br>
<br>
  I was taking about 80 points of damage per second from burning lava, and if you dont swim well you wont make it.  IT takes about 10-15 seconds to get out of the lava.<br>
<br>
  What to expect:  Angry, red mobs.  Red as in skin color, and unless you are over level 50, they probably con that too.  First up, Kobolds, both melees and casters.  Then big imps like the ones found in Sol B but a little tougher, tentacle-terror looking things that eat the terrors found in Najena and Crystal Caverns as a snack.  Living magma can be seen popping out of the pools of lava and chasing the damsels around if they get too close.  Then there are some ... well lets say Imps that look like they got hit by lightening ... wings all tattered, emaciated... sharp talons.<br>
<br>
  Named mobs:  yes!  I saw several but only remmeber the name of one (Pulsating Pool of Magma).  Decent drops too, my group killed a named imp and got a Ring of the Firesoul (AC 7, Str/Wis/Int/save vs Magic all +5, Dex/Agi both +4, HP/Mana both +40. wt 0.0, wearable by all, recommended level of 50, Lore Item, is NOT no drop).  But I didn't win the roll (raises an angry fist to the uncaring Gods!).<br>
<br>
Got to some mob named something like Culeth the Gatekeeper, at which point a storng force of about 12 members of Valon came barging past us.  Did I mention that they dropped about 4 mobs onto us to deal with as they hustled by?  So we were sitting there taking care of their mess, while they moved forward to tackle the BIG guy (was red to a lvl 65 player... both in color and as a con).  Anyhow, Valon put up a good fight, and died.  Their cleric (at least I think it was a cleric, kinda hard to tell from the panicked look an his face as he was running with about 6 guardians on his tail -- right towards our group!)  ran smack to us and was slain (alas) at our feet, luckily the mobs turned tail when they saw our group (Actually, they turned to go back to finish off one of the last Valon pepole standing).  My group thought best to succor at that moment.. and did.<br>
<br>
Then, I experienced the true wrath of the uncaring Norrathian Gods.  Or maybe it was Brell, taking revenge.  The succor spell didn't pick me up; I was left standing there, with perhaps an almost as shocking panicked look on my face as the Valon cleric had.  My party was safely carried away, and I quickly scrambled to mem my gate spell.<br>
<br>
Will Mugo escape the grasp of Culeth and his minions, or will he succom to the scortching touch of this Uber mob?<br>
<br>
